title.narrative: Output 3.3: Protection – System Strengthening“National capacity to legislate, plan, monitor and budget for child protection prevention and response, including for children on the move, is strengthened.”

description.narrative: Several policy initiatives were undertaken to strengthen the national capacity to legislate, plan and monitor child protection prevention and response. They included the development of the National Action Plan on EVAC, completion of the profiling study of social work force, development of a social work force accreditation framework, increased political buy-in on the issue of FGM evident through public statements by the Government of Egypt and the amendments to the existing SOP on children on the move. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
